text: Saintigny is a commune in the Eure-et-Loir department in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint- Denis-d'Authou (the seat) and Frétigny.Arrêté préfectoral 19 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Eure-et-Loir department ==References== Category:Communes of Eure-et-Loir
title: Saintigny
